format: Gorsuc (1997) suggested an alternative model for factor extension.  His method is appropriate for the case of repeated variables.  This is handled in link{fa.extension} with correct=FALSE
title: Example data set from Gorsuch (1997) for an example factor extension.
description:
Description
Gorsuch (1997) suggests an alternative to the classic Dwyer (1937) factor extension technique.  This data set is taken from that article.  Useful for comparing link{fa.extension} with and without the correct=TRUE option.
